"""
This script compares the performance of all binary and multiclass models using non‑parametric rank tests and a critical difference diagram.

It:

Loads the binary and multiclass cross‑validation results from SI_1_ML_Results_Binary_Multiclass.xlsx and trims each sheet to the relevant metric and misclassification columns.

Builds a composite score per fold and model (0.4×accuracy + 0.4×mean/macro F1 + 0.2×(1 − loss)) for the binary task (Frost vs Non‑frost) and for the multiclass task (Blocky, Granular, Platy‑lenticular).

Pivots these into Fold × Model tables, then runs a Friedman test and post‑hoc Nemenyi test to obtain average ranks and pairwise significance for all models in each task.

Uses a custom plot_cd_subplot function to draw a critical difference (CD) diagram for binary (top panel) and multiclass (bottom panel): models are placed on a rank axis with colored labels, and thick horizontal bars connect pairs that are not significantly different at α = 0.05.

Saves the combined CD diagram as a 300 dpi .tif file (combined_critical_difference_diagram.tif) and prints the Friedman statistics, p‑values, average ranks, and critical differences for both tasks.
"""
